The paper proposes a deep learning approach for image spam detection using convolutional neural networks, which falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The paper also discusses the security aspect of image spam, which falls under the cryptography and security (cs.CR) sub-category. Additionally, the paper uses a dataset of images, which falls under the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category, and the classification task involves image recognition, which falls under the information retrieval (cs.IR) sub-category.
